    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-07-25T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-07-25T04:00:00-05:00" n="418"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d418">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/4831: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-07-25T12:00:00+03:00"
                            >July 25, 1940—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 3:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>902. The British Military Attaché formerly assigned to Riga and now en route to
                    London via the Soviet Union states that Soviet troops are believed to be
                    distributed in the Baltic States as follows: Estonia: 150,000 men, 400 planes,
                    and 500 tanks including 6 infantry divisions; Latvia: 200,000 men, 1000 tanks,
                    500 planes, including 12 divisions and 5 tank brigades; Lithuania: 200,000,
                    including 1000 tanks, 500 planes including 6 divisions, 1 cavalry corps and 6
                    tank brigades. The Air Corps includes 4 bomber and 4 pursuit regiments.</p>
                <p>Major Yeaton<note n="97" xml:id="d418fn97">Maj. Ivan D. Yeaton, American Military
                        Attaché in the Soviet Union.</note> has been advised by his British
                    colleague that the War Office at London has informed the British Embassy in
                    Moscow <pb facs="0417" n="405" xml:id="pg_405"/> that the Germans are moving
                    about 40 divisions into East Prussia and Poland.</p>
                <p>Please inform the War Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
